        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fully tilt the cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify if the incorrect tube is installed (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590402">Figure 2</hotlnk>). If the vehicle has the correct lower dip stick tube,
                    no further repair should be performed. If the tube is incorrect, complete the following:
                </para>
                <figure id="f9590402" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9590402" filename="../afcfigures/g9590402.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the dip stick (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unthread the lower dip stick tube from the engine block (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolt, flat washer, lockwasher and nut that secure the cushioned clamp to the
                    tube mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the dip stick assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the tube nut on the union that secures the lower tube section to the complete dip
                    stick tube assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower section of the dip stick tube from the tube assembly and replace it
                    with the new lower section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590402">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Tighten the tube nut finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread the lower end of the new tube into the engine block finger tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refasten the assembly cushioned tube clamp to the mounting bracket with the bolt, flat
                    washer, lockwasher and nut removed in Step 5. Tighten the nut to 80-110 in-lbs. (9-12 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the lower end tube nut into the engine block.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the tube nut on the union that secures the lower section to the upper section of
                    the dip stick tube assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9590401">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the dip stick.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower the cab.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
